debugger-ui-protocol-and-dumb — Phase 5: UI protocol + dumb-terminal UI
=======================================================================

See also:
  clautolisp/documentation/clautolisp-debugger-implementation-plan.org (Phase 5)
  clautolisp/documentation/clautolisp-debugger-spec.org (§17, §18, §21–§24, §26)
  issues/open/debugger-inspector.issue, debugger-snapshot-stepping.issue

Context
-------

The debugger is UI-agnostic; UIs are interchangeable CLOS classes
implementing a fixed protocol. The dumb-terminal UI is the lowest common
denominator (serial line, M-x shell, CI) AND the bring-up UI used to
validate every engine phase. "If a feature can't be expressed here, it
probably shouldn't be a core debugger feature" (spec §18.3).

Scope / deliverables
--------------------

1. New system `clautolisp/autolisp-debug-ui`, package `clautolisp.debug.ui`:
   - Debugger->UI notifications: ui-attached/detached, ui-thread-hit,
     ui-thread-unhandled-error, ui-thread-caught-error, ui-thread-resumed,
     ui-thread-exited, ui-breakpoint-added/removed, ui-show-source,
     ui-show-message (spec §17.1). Default method NIL.
   - UI->debugger commands: cmd-continue, cmd-step {in,out,over,call,finish},
     cmd-advance, cmd-set/remove/list-breakpoint, cmd-select-frame, cmd-eval,
     cmd-set-variable, cmd-inspect, cmd-inspector-{descend,up,bind,
     path-expression}, cmd-workspace-{list,clear}, cmd-disable-thread-debug,
     cmd-attach-thread (spec §17.2).
   - Session lifecycle: start-session / with-session / attach-thread /
     multiple threads / teardown (spec §21–§24); `*protocol-version*` check
     at attach (spec §27).

2. New system `clautolisp/autolisp-debug-ui-dumb`, package `clautolisp.ui.dumb`
   (spec §18): line-by-line tagged output, DBG> sub-REPL with single-letter
   commands (c/s/i/o/f/n/b/B/p/e/l/t/q/h), bare `(form)` = eval-in-frame,
   numeric repeat args; numbered source listing with `>>` current marker;
   inspector in dumb terminal (spec §18.2) with descend/up/eval/copy-path/bind.

Acceptance
----------

- Full break -> inspect -> step -> continue session over plain stdin/stdout,
  usable in CI and over a pipe.
- Conformance per spec §26 MUST items satisfied.
- FiveAM tests; `*version*` bumped.

* Resolution (triage 2026-07-23)

Shipped: autolisp-debug-ui protocol.lisp + the dumb terminal UI, 400+ tests; the interactor framework now drives its loops.
